  "summary": "While Roger and Frankie are discussing Dr. Nicholson's influence and their efforts to prevent Henry Baskington-French from traveling to Grange, a gunshot rings out from inside the house. They rush to the hallway and find a pale Sylvia Baskington-French. Because the study door is locked, Roger breaks a window to gain entry. Inside, they discover Henry sprawled across his desk with a gunshot wound to his temple and a revolver on the floor.\n\nDr. Nicholson arrives shortly after the discovery and examines the body, declaring Henry dead. He notes a suicide note near Henry's elbow in which Henry expresses an inability to fight a \"deadly habit\" and offers blessings to Sylvia and Tommy. Frankie eventually finds the study key in Henry's outer coat pocket, which allows her to unlock the door from the hallway.\n\nThe following morning, Frankie meets with Bobby to discuss the incident. While Frankie maintains that Henry committed suicide—noting that the door was locked and the window was shut—Bobby expresses suspicion. He suggests that Dr. Nicholson may have murdered Henry, forced him to write the note, and then staged his arrival. Bobby points out that Nicholson was the one who \"found\" the key in Henry's pocket, implying the discovery could have been faked. Frankie counters this by insisting she was watching Nicholson closely and is certain the key was in the pocket.",
